SIMPLE: sigillaria
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sigillaria
<hw>Sig`il*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.,
from <ets>sigillum</ets> a seal. See <er>Sigil</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Rom.
Antic.)</fld> <def>Little images or figures of earthenware exposed for
sale, or given as presents, on the last two days of the Saturnalia;
hence, the last two, or the sixth and seventh, days of the
Saturnalia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sigillaria</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sigillaria
<hw>Sig`il*la"ri*a</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fem sing. fr. L.
<ets>sigillum</ets> a seal.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
fossil trees principally found in the coal formation; -- so named from
the seallike leaf scars in vertical rows on the surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sigillarid</ent>⟦br⟧
